¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Why} ⦉

  ‖ We generalize convex functions to $𝗥^n$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Definition} ⦉

  ‖ Let $A$ be a convex subset of $𝗥^n$. ⦉

  ‖ The function $f: A → 𝗥$ is ❬convex❭ if for any $a, b ∈
    A$ and $t ∈ [0, 1]$,
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(ta + (1-t)b) ≤ tf(a) + (1-t)f(b). ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ It is ❬concave❭ if $-f$ is convex. ⦉
⦉

